            </span>
            <span id="First_Paragraph_Mod">
            In my childhood we couldn’t afford eggs, so when we got two eggs, it was like a celebration for the season. We had to mix the eggs with twice as much water and put sugar in it so that the eggs were enough to share among all of us kids. Many nights we went to sleep hungry. <br />
            </span>
