            <br />We had no money to buy a mattress. We slept on the wood—bare wood. Every night there were fleas coming out of the wood and biting us. When we caught them we squeezed them and the blood would come out, because they sucked the blood out of our bodies. Those are called wood fleas. There were a lot of them. We were lucky any night we weren’t bitten by those wood fleas.<br />
            </span>
