                    </div>
                </div>
                <span id="Chapter_Quote_Mod">
                “For us to step outside the bus and go to our house, which was twenty steps, was the scariest part of our day.”
                </span>
            </div>

            <span id="Second_Paragraph_Mod">
            I think the most horrific situation that I faced was that there were always a bunch of teenage boys sitting outside our house, smoking marijuana and dope. They were swearing and using all kinds of words. They would sit right outside our house, so for us to step outside the bus and go to our house, which was twenty steps, was the scariest part of our day. We had to shoot into the door and shoot inside the house. I still remember those teenage boys would steal our underwear from our yard, and then they would trample them underneath the soil underneath the house and smoke marijuana with it. We were horrified by losing our clothes. We didn’t know where our clothing went sometimes.<br />

            <br />Going to school we only had 25 cents for lunch, but even with only 25 cents we were at a very high risk of being bullied and they would take away our 25 cents. Usually, instead of taking a bus to school, I would walk to school so I could save my 25 cents for lunch.<br />
