            </span>
            <span id="Contributor_Name_Mod">
            evelyn li
            </span>
            <span id="First_Paragraph_Mod">
            I didn’t decide to be a doctor. God did. I have to admit that during the years that we were growing up, healthcare issues were a primary setback in our continual poverty. My brother and I were always alternating having seizures when we were in Hong Kong. My mom, having no car to take us to the hospital, had to beg the neighbor to take us, and many times our neighbor would say no. That really scared her. I remember getting sewing needles poked through my finger, and my dad had no money to take me to the hospital. He would pull out the needle and put all kinds of powders on it, and miraculously it healed. 
            <br />
            </span>
            <div id="boxmodex3" class="clearfix">
                <div class="ChapterVideoDivMod">
                    <div class="ChapterVideoMod">
                        <!--iframe src="//player.vimeo.com/video/113120001" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" webkitallowfullscreen mozallowfullscreen allowfullscreen></iframe-->
